The paper deals with low rank approximation and matrix decomposition, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of error correcting codes also suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of these techniques in solving least squares regression problems, which falls under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
